Moreover, "saturation" may now be understood as a function of the
"relative amounts of chromatic and achromatic responses."
Hence,
<p>
<blockquote>
At the two spectral extremes where the chromatic responses are large relative to
the white response, the spectral saturation is high.
</blockquote>
