<h3>Color Constancy (Optional Topic)</h3>
In the context of trichromatic color theory,
an object's color is dependent upon the the color of the light which illuminates it.
For example, a red apple lit by a blue light should appear purple.
<p>
However, it appears that the brain has a built-in mechanism to filter out
lighting conditions and interpret (unconsciously) the "true" color of an object.
